permalink: /Modern Nature Poetry in Poland (Early 20th century)/Jan Lechoń/Jan Lechoń - Wild Things
---

In deep forests, the wild things,
Roam free beneath the trees,
A world untouched by echoes,
Of man’s harsh memories.

Life thrives in every corner,
In shadows and in light,
Nature’s sacred keepers,
Guarding day and night.

- Jan Lechoń
